title: For Sale:  M38 Carcano
postcontent: For sale is an M38 Carcano short rifle in 7.35 mm. It was originally built as an M1891 long rifle in 1917 at the Roma arsenal, then converted in 1939 at Terni by having the barrel cut and rebored. The bore is in good overall condition, with some light pitting and frosting. The rifle has no import marks, so it came into the country prior to 1968, and was a veteran bringback. The stock has been refinished, and everything but the barreled action has been chrome or nickel plated. Included with the rifle is one en bloc clip and 16 rounds of WWII vintage ammo. Make reasonable cash offer or trade for other surplus firearms.
